-- Sun Pharmaceutical Advances in Mumbai After Drug Gets Initial FDA Approval
-- B y   S u r e s h   S e s h a d r i
-- 2010-12-31T03:49:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-31/sun-pharmaceutical-advances-in-mumbai-after-drug-gets-initial-fda-approval.html
  Sun Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd .
climbed in Mumbai trading after India’s largest drugmaker by
market value said it received initial approval from the U.S.
Food and Drug Administration for a copy of Roche Holding AG’s
osteoporosis drug Boniva.  The stock rose 1.3 percent to 488.90 rupees as of 9:18 a.m.
local time.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Suresh Seshadri at 
 sseshadri1@bloomberg.net  